@page "/gear.html"

<LayoutView Layout="typeof(Layout)">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Main Camera</h2>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony A7R5</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                63MP full-frame mirrorless interchangable lens camera
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 24mm f/1.4 GM</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                24mm prime wide angle lens. Currently my favourite lens, it spends a lot of time attached to my camera
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 85mm f/1.8</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Nice and compact 85mm prime lens, its size and weight means it's nearly always in my bag
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 16-35mm f/2.8 GM</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                16-35mm wide angle lens. Used to be my favourite lens before I got the 24mm
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Tamron 28-75mm f/2.8</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                General purpose lens, great for everything, even macro stuff!
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 70-200mm f/4 G</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Small, lightweight telephoto zoom. I chose it over the f/2.8 GM because of the price and weight, since I mostly shooting landscapes I'm stopped down to f/8 anyway.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 200-600mm F5.6-6.3 G</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Super telephoto lens, mostly for wildlife photos but comes in strangely useful for landscape photography.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Other Camera</h2>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony RX100V</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                I use this for video and timelapses. It can do 4k and 1000 fps (not at the same time unfortunately) and is tiny.
                Even with 6 spare batteries it is lighter than most of my lenses!
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Ultrapod II</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Awesome tiny tripod. I quite often use it as a handle when videoing on the move.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Accessories</h2>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Tripod</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                No brand, nothing special, tripod off Amazon. Made of aluminium with a ball head & arca-swiss mount. Main requirement is that is light and packs down small.
                Currently looking a carbon fibre replacement
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Arca-swiss L-braket</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Best accessory ever. Seriously... I was amazed at how useful it was to be able to attach the camera to the tripod how I wanted, when I wanted.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Remote</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                MultiUSB remote, for avoiding any extra vibrations and taking exposures >30 seconds.
                Think it was the cheapest on Amazon
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Filters</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                I also have 82mm CPL, ND200, ND1000 filters and various adapters so I can attach them to everything but the 200-600 (it has a 95mm filter!).
                For the 200-600 I have an ND100000 just for those times when I want to point my camera at our closest star.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Headtorch</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Petzl Reactik+, small powerful headtorch with USB charging & bluetooth. I didn't realise how good adaptive beams where until I disabled it.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Power bank(s)</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Just so many...
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Graveyard</h2>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony 24-240mm f/3.5-6.3</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Was the first lens I got. Super versatile but slowly got replaced by higher quality, more specific lenses. Sold on eBay.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Samyang 24mm f/1.4</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Second lens I bought. I was drawn in by the wide angle & aperture for astrophotography. I was never able to get any good shots because I hadn't got the hang of manual focus yet. Sold on eBay.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sigma 150-600mm f/5-6.3 (C, Canon)</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                Super telephoto lens that I used to use for landscapes & wildlife. Traded it in for the Sony 200-600mm.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card mb-4 box-shadow">
        <img class="card-img-top" src="https://placehold.co/350x350" alt="Placeholder">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Sony A7R2</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-justify">
                My previous camera body, it was great for static subjects but it kept missing focus on anything that moved.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</div>
</LayoutView>